  <summary>6/29/1995--Introduced.
Consumer Auto-Tax Relief Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a deduction for interest on the acquisition of an automobile: (1) of which 60 percent or more of its equipment originated in the United States or Canada; (2) the price of which is under $35,000; and (3) the sale of which is its first retail sale.</summary>
